posts.title: I Was Just Illegally Prevented from Voting in Texas! I Just Uncovered Election Fraud in Texas.
posts.content:
I went to in person early voting this morning in Texas and was told that I would not be able to vote, even though I lawfully and properly registered to vote. I tried to vote at the Wilco Hutto Annex polling location on 321 Ed Schmidt BLVD.

My wife and I both registered to vote in Texas this year before the registration deadline, though it was marginally close to the deadline. We moved to Texas somewhat recently. I sent in my voter registration before my wife did.

When I went to vote this morning, I was told that I would not be allowed to vote because my voter registration certificate has a valid date of 11/09/2024, which is after the election. My wife’s voter registration certificate has a valid date of 11/05/2024, which means it is valid on election day. I sent my registration in before my Wife, yet somehow mine came back with a valid date after the election, 11/09/2024. I am a registered member of the Republican Party, and my wife is not a registered member of any party.

My Hypothesis: My voter registration certificate came back with a valid date after the election because I am a registered Republican. My Wife’s voter registration certificate came back with the correct valid date because she is not a registered republican.

At the polling location, I first started working with a regular poll worker, but I was then passed off to someone in a supervisor position. The poll supervisor tried to get me to leave a provisional ballot, but I do not believe for a second that my provisional ballot would be counted as a vote for President Trump. I am very good at reading people. I could see the fear in the poll supervisor’s eyes when I refused to leave a provisional ballot and told him that I will be researching this.

I believe that this is a form of election fraud to get people to leave provisional ballots that will either be changed or destroyed.
